cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with visual question answering and generation, which are tasks related to computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, since the paper also proposes a joint learning framework and uses regular terms to guide the training process, it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses parameter sharing and dual learning, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper deals with generating questions and answers, it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with natural language processing and information retrieval.
